# Owlat VPS Environment Configuration
# Generated by Owlat Control Plane

# ── Convex ──
INSTANCE_SECRET={{INSTANCE_SECRET}}
CONVEX_ADMIN_KEY={{CONVEX_ADMIN_KEY}}
CONTROL_PLANE_URL={{CONTROL_PLANE_URL}}

# ── Redis ──
REDIS_PASSWORD={{REDIS_PASSWORD}}

# ── MTA ──
MTA_API_KEY={{MTA_API_KEY}}
MTA_WEBHOOK_SECRET={{MTA_WEBHOOK_SECRET}}
EHLO_HOSTNAME=mail.{{SLUG}}.owlat.app
RETURN_PATH_DOMAIN=bounces.{{SLUG}}.owlat.app
BOUNCE_VERP_KEY={{BOUNCE_VERP_KEY}}
IP_POOLS_TRANSACTIONAL=0.0.0.0
IP_POOLS_CAMPAIGN=0.0.0.0
DKIM_KEYS={}

# ── Mail Sync (external IMAP/SMTP accounts — mail.external flag) ──
# Shared secret between Convex and the mail-sync worker. The Convex deployment
# also needs MAIL_SYNC_API_URL=http://mail-sync:3200 and MAIL_SYNC_API_KEY set
# as function env vars (alongside MTA_API_URL) so outbound external sends and
# the /test credential check reach the worker.
MAIL_SYNC_API_KEY={{MAIL_SYNC_API_KEY}}
# Messages per descending UID batch when importing a mailbox's history during a
# "Migrate from Google" migration. Lower it on tiny VPSes; raise it to import
# large mailboxes faster. Optional — defaults to 200.
# MAIL_SYNC_BACKFILL_BATCH=200

# ── Web ──
NUXT_PUBLIC_CONVEX_URL=http://localhost:3210
NUXT_PUBLIC_CONVEX_SITE_URL=http://localhost:3211
NUXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=https://app.owlat.app/{{SLUG}}

# ── Local LLM / Ollama (optional, "ai-worker" profile) ──
# The bundled `ollama` service runs under the same profile as the AI worker, so
# it activates when the `ai` feature flag is on. It is reachable only on the
# internal Docker network as ollama:11434 (no published host port). Pin the image
# tag here if you don't want :latest:
# OLLAMA_VERSION=latest
#
# To use it, set these Convex *function* env vars on the backend (convex env set):
#   LLM_PROVIDER=ollama
#   LLM_BASE_URL=http://ollama:11434/v1   # auto-resolved when LLM_PROVIDER=ollama
# No LLM_API_KEY is required for Ollama.

# ── Rate limiting (public endpoints) — STRONGLY RECOMMENDED ──
# Per-IP rate limiting on the public form / unsubscribe / preferences / DOI /
# tracking / webhook endpoints only works when the backend can trust a forwarded
# client-IP header. Set this Convex *function* env var (convex env set) so the
# limiter keys on the real client IP instead of a single shared bucket:
#   RATE_LIMIT_TRUSTED_PROXY=xforwarded
# This VPS fronts the backend with Caddy, which appends the client IP to
# X-Forwarded-For, so `xforwarded` (read from the right) is correct. Use
# `cloudflare` if Cloudflare terminates TLS instead — but note `cloudflare` /
# `xrealip` trust their header unconditionally, so also firewall the backend to
# the proxy's IP ranges (otherwise a direct request can forge it). `xforwarded`
# is bypass-resistant. Leaving it UNSET is fail-safe against spoofing but makes
# the limits coarse (one shared bucket), so a flood on a cheap public path can
# throttle others.

# ── PostHog analytics (analytics.posthog flag) ──
# Set both as Convex *function* env vars (convex env set) to pipe product events
# to a PostHog instance. Optional — the app works without them.
#   POSTHOG_API_KEY=phc_...
#   POSTHOG_HOST=https://eu.i.posthog.com

# ── URL reputation (scan.urls flag) ──
# Google Safe Browsing API key — checks outbound links before sending. Optional;
# set as a Convex *function* env var (convex env set).
#   GOOGLE_SAFE_BROWSING_API_KEY=
